33:48.260 --> 33:57.569 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now to a battle
emerging in
some states over schools and
rights for transgender

33:57.602 --> 33:59.337 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
students.

33:59.371 --> 34:03.508 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
South Dakota's governor, Dennis
Daugaard,
must decide by tomorrow whether
he will sign

34:03.541 --> 34:09.014 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
or veto a bill that would make
his state the
first in the country to restrict
transgender

34:09.047 --> 34:14.819 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
students' access to school
restrooms and locker
rooms. If he doesn't act by
tomorrow, the

34:14.853 --> 34:16.221 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
bill will become law.

34:16.254 --> 34:20.525 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The "NewsHour"'s April Brown
reports for our
American Graduate team.

34:20.558 --> 34:25.363 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
APRIL BROWN: Transgender rights
advocates
in South Dakota gathered at the
state capitol

34:25.397 --> 34:29.668 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
building last week to draw
attention to a
bill they consider
discriminatory.

34:29.701 --> 34:31.469 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Freshman Nathan Leonard was
there.

34:31.503 --> 34:34.739 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NATHAN LEONARD, Student: It
directly affects
me, because I am a transgender
student, and

34:34.773 --> 34:36.508 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I already get made fun of
enough.

34:36.541 --> 34:39.444 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
APRIL BROWN: The bill would
require school
restrooms and locker rooms are
"used only

34:39.477 --> 34:44.382 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
by students of the same
biological sex." It
would also allow students whose
gender identity

34:44.416 --> 34:49.654 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
is different than their
biological sex "to
be provided with a reasonable
accommodation."

34:49.688 --> 34:53.658 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One of the bill's primary
sponsors, state
Representative Fred Deutsch,
says the goal

34:53.692 --> 34:55.527 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
is to protect children.

34:55.560 --> 34:58.029 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DEUTSCH (R), South Dakota
State Representative:
The bill is not intended to hurt
or harm.

34:58.063 --> 35:04.869 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm protecting their hearts,
their eyes and
their minds. I don't want our
children to

35:04.903 --> 35:07.339 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
be exposed to the anatomy of
other genders.

35:07.372 --> 35:11.910 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
APRIL BROWN: But many in the
LGBT community
and their supporters believe the
bill would

35:11.943 --> 35:15.714 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
not protect children, especially
transgender
students.

35:15.747 --> 35:19.417 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
State Representative Paula Hawks
opposes the
bill and stood with protesters.

35:19.451 --> 35:25.190 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAULA HAWKS (D), South Dakota
State Representative:
It is an unfriendly message.
It's hostile.

35:25.223 --> 35:28.126 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's unacceptable in a state
where we're trying
to progress forward.

35:28.159 --> 35:32.030 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
APRIL BROWN: The battle comes as
a number
of cities have expanded
nondiscrimination

35:32.063 --> 35:37.602 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
laws for transgender people. But
there are
many other bills many consider
anti-transgender

35:37.635 --> 35:43.308 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
pending in 16 states, including
Virginia,
Illinois, Indiana, and
Washington state. And

35:43.341 --> 35:47.879 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
some of them would restrict
students' access
to restrooms and sports
programs.

35:47.912 --> 35:51.916 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The South Dakota legislation is
also at odds
with guidance from the U.S.
Department of

35:51.950 --> 35:56.121 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
