didn't allow
transgender students to use
their preferred

36:00.859 --> 36:02.694 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
bathrooms and changing areas.

36:02.727 --> 36:07.732 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
However, the Department of
Education guidance
is not legally binding. And if
Governor Dennis

36:07.766 --> 36:11.336 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Daugaard signs the bill, there
could be another
repercussion: lawsuits.

36:11.369 --> 36:16.674 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DEUTSCH: This is a values
issue. And
if we protect our children and
we get sued,

36:16.708 --> 36:18.777 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
well, then that's the decision
we make.

36:18.810 --> 36:22.580 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
APRIL BROWN: The final
decision-maker, Governor
Daugaard, met with transgender
students and

36:22.614 --> 36:26.251 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
their parents last week, which
he says put
a human face on the issue.

36:26.284 --> 36:31.556 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GOV. DENNIS DAUGAARD (R), South
Dakota: I
heard their personal stories.
And so I saw

36:31.589 --> 36:36.628 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
things through their eyes, in
that sense.
It's certainly of great concern
to many people.

36:36.661 --> 36:44.302 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Certainly, to the opponents of
the bill, it's
of great concern. And so I don't
treat it

36:44.335 --> 36:46.004 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
lightly, by any means.

36:46.037 --> 36:49.174 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
APRIL BROWN: LGBT advocates at
the capitol
were pleased the governor
listened.

36:49.207 --> 36:55.680 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: Any time you're talking,
the door's
open for change. When there's no
discussion,

36:55.713 --> 36:57.649 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
you're not going forward.

36:57.682 --> 37:01.152 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
APRIL BROWN: Governor Daugaard
has also spoken
to the bill's sponsors and is
reviewing testimony

37:01.186 --> 37:03.788 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and court documents before he
makes his final
decision.

37:03.822 --> 37:11.029 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
April Brown.

37:11.062 --> 37:25.844 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Over the weekend,
several hundred
hostages of the Nigerian
Islamist group Boko

37:25.877 --> 37:31.149 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Haram were freed. It happened
during a raid
by Nigerian and Cameroonian
forces along the

37:31.182 --> 37:33.918 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
border between the two African
nations.

37:33.952 --> 37:39.591 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The raid comes as the U.S.
military has moved
to increase cooperation with
regional governments

37:39.624 --> 37:44.829 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to fight the jihadist group.
Boko Haram pledged
allegiance to the Islamic State
group, or

37:44.863 --> 37:51.469 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ISIS, last year. According to
Amnesty International,
the six-year uprising has killed
more than

37:51.503 --> 37:56.941 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
20,000 people. Another 2.8
million have been
forced from their homes in
Nigeria, Cameroon,

37:56.975 --> 37:58.977 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Niger, and Chad.

37:59.010 --> 38:05.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Boko Haram gained worldwide
infamy in 2014
after kidnapping more than 200
schoolgirls

38:05.850 --> 38:11.723 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from the town of Chibok in
Northeastern Nigeria.
That sparked a global campaign
to free the

38:11.756 --> 38:17.162 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
girls, with the hashtag
#BringBackOurGirls
as a social media rallying cry.
The girls'

38:17.195 --> 38:23.434 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
plight was a contributing factor
to then-President
Goodluck Jonathan's election
loss last year.

38:23.468 --> 38:28.940 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The U.S. has military personnel
operating
a new drone base in Cameroon to
provide intelligence.

38:28.973 --> 38:34.245 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And there is now discussion of
sending American
special forces near the front
lines of Nigeria's

38:34.279 --> 38:38.716 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
fight against Boko Haram. They
would advise
the military in its operations.

38:38.750 --> 38:42.754 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm joined now by special
correspondent Nick
Schifrin. He's currently on
assignment for

38:42.787 --> 38:48.593 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
us in Nairobi, Kenya, and he
reported in-depth
from Nigeria for the "NewsHour"
last year.

38:48.626 --> 38:50.695 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Nick, it's good to talk to you
again.

38:50.728 --> 38:53.798 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, tell us what you know about
this new U.S.
engagement in Nigeria.

38:53.831 --> 38:56.501 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
NICK SCHIFRIN: Yes, Gwen, good
evening.

38:56.534 --> 39:02.807 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's a new recommendation by
the U.S. military's
top Africa Command that one to
three dozen

39:02.840 --> 39:07.545 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
special operations forces troops
be deployed
to Northeastern Nigeria. This is
what the

39:07.579 --> 39:10.615 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
military calls an
advise-and-assist mission.

39:10.648 --> 39:15.286 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They are towards the front
lines, but not
really on the front lines,
advising the Nigerian

39:15.320 --> 39:20.658 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
military in their fight,
assisting that fight,
things like intelligence and
training those

39:20.692 --> 39:23.962 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
troops. Now, this is just a
recommendation
right now. This will have to go
through the

39:23.995 --> 39:26.464 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
State Department and the
Pentagon and the
White House.

39:26.497 --> 39:32.003 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But this is what the military in
Africa wants.
And it's what one military
official describes

39:32.036 --> 39:37.308 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
as a national progression to a
real escalation
in what the U.S. has been doing
against Boko

39:37.342 --> 39:41.646 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Haram and helping the Nigerians.
The first
step in that is intelligence.
There's a new

39:41.679 --> 39:49.320 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
drone base in nearby Northern
Cameroon. Predator
drones have been supplying the
Nigerian and

39:49.354 --> 39:54.525 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the countries all along the Lake
Chad Basin
with imagery, with intelligence,
so they can

39:54.559 --> 39:56.294 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
go after Boko Haram.

39:56.327 --> 40:00.131 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's new in the last few
months. And just
in the last few years, the U.S.
has resumed

40:00.164 --> 40:06.404 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
a training mission in
Northwestern Nigeria.
That is for Nigerian special
forces far from

40:06.437 --> 40:10.808 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the front line. That's a mission
the U.S.
has really been trying to resume
after it

40:10.842 --> 40:12.543 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ended about a year ago.

40:12.577 --> 40:17.315 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, Gwen this is in addition to
real concerted
effort diplomatically to try and
help the

40:17.348 --> 40:21.953 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Nigerians improve things like
the police.
So, this is a real escalation in
the U.S.

40:21.986 --> 40:24.422 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
helping Nigeria and all the
countries fighting
Boko Haram.

40:24.455 --> 40:29.027 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: It seems like one of
the big differences
between then and now is the
presence of a

40:29.060 --> 40:31.296 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
new Nigerian president,
Muhammadu Buhari.

40:31.329 --> 40:35.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NICK SCHIFRIN: Yes, it's an
extraordinary
difference, a real sea change of
a difference

40:35.900 --> 40:37.635 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
when he was elected.

40:37.669 --> 40:40.905 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Just to give you a sense, Gwen,
of how bad
the relationship between the
U.S. and Nigeria

40:40.938 --> 40:46.210 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
was before his election, at one
point, the
top U.S. military official in
Africa refused

40:46.244 --> 40:51.482 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
to shake the hand of the
Nigerian chief of
army staff. That's how bad that
relationship

40:51.516 --> 40:53.318 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
was.

40:53.351 --> 40:56.321 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One of the U.S. deputies was
actually locked
out of a Nigerian base at one
point, a kind

40:56.354 --> 41:00.992 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of message by the Nigerians that
they were
upset. Since then, total sea
change. Muhammadu

41:01.025 --> 41:05.830 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Buhari has not only changed the
heads of the
military, so the actual
officials doing this

41:05.863 --> 41:08.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
work, and that relationship has
improved between
the U.S.

41:08.733 --> 41:13.571 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But he's really said to all of
his deputies,
look, the U.S. is our ally. We
need to work

41:13.604 --> 41:15.273 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
with them against Boko Haram.

41:15.306 --> 41:19.277 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Let's talk about the
strength
of Boko Haram. How strong are
they and how

41:19.310 --> 41:21.045 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
extensive is their influence?

41:21.079 --> 41:24.949 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NICK SCHIFRIN: At one point,
Boko Haram was
the deadliest terrorist group in
the world.

41:24.982 --> 41:27.618 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That was by 2014, by the numbers
of people
killed.

41:27.652 --> 41:31.923 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it's important, Gwen, to
note that that
was less about Boko Haram than
about the Nigerian

41:31.956 --> 41:37.295 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
military. In some sense, Boko
Haram didn't
really have a foe on the
battlefield. Nigerian

41:37.328 --> 41:42.834 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
soldiers were going out without
bullets, without
shoes, without the actual
material they needed

41:42.867 --> 41:44.635 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to fight Boko Haram.

41:44.669 --> 41:49.974 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so Boko Haram was able to
take over land,
was able to kill so many people
because it

41:50.007 --> 41:56.280 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
really wasn't encountering the
Nigerian military
or any of the militaries in the
region. Now

41:56.314 --> 42:00.518 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that's not changed not only in
Nigeria. But
Chad, Niger, Cameroon, they have
all come

42:00.551 --> 42:04.255 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
together, with a little bit of
U.S. help,
to face Boko Haram.

42:04.288 --> 42:08.926 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's clear that, right now,
Boko Haram
is on the back foot. It cannot
seize any land

42:08.960 --> 42:13.531 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
anymore, even as it still
launches suicide
attacks that are still deadly in
Nigeria.

42:13.564 --> 42:18.236 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Finally, Nick, for
many Americans,
the last thing they heard about
this question

42:18.269 --> 42:24.142 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of Boko Haram's strength in
Nigeria has centered
around hostage-taking,
specifically about

42:24.175 --> 42:25.977 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
those Chibok girls.

42:26.010 --> 42:30.081 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Where does this stand now? We
keep hearing
that thousands of hostages have
been released,

42:30.114 --> 42:31.983 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
but not so much about the girls.

42:32.016 --> 42:36.320 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NICK SCHIFRIN: Yes, this is
another example
of how Boko Haram is still
around, but weakened.

42:36.354 --> 42:40.958 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tens of thousand of people were
taken hostage
by Boko Haram at its peak.
Thousands of them

42:40.992 --> 42:45.563 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
have been released by the
Nigerian military,
by the Chadian military, who are
going into

42:45.596 --> 42:47.532 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
former Boko Haram strongholds.

42:47.565 --> 42:52.503 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the girls themselves are
still missing.
President Buhari says he is
willing to negotiate

42:52.537 --> 42:57.642 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with Boko Haram to release those
girls. He's
willing to release Boko Haram
prisoners, but

42:57.675 --> 43:01.913 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he says that he hasn't found the
right Boko
Haram negotiators to do that.

43:01.946 --> 43:06.484 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, right now, those girls are
still missing.
And, Gwen, as you know, such a
tragic part

43:06.517 --> 43:10.955 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of the story, some of those
girls or girls
in general being kidnapped are
now being used

43:10.988 --> 43:13.424 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
as suicide bombers in some of
these attacks.

43:13.458 --> 43:17.862 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, there is a still a very big
effort by
the U.S. and Nigeria to find
those girls,

43:17.895 --> 43:20.998 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
but so long after those
kidnappings, there's
still no sign of them.

43:21.032 --> 43:30.975 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Reporting for us
tonight, Nick
Schifrin. Thank you.

43:31.008 --> 43:38.082 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
NICK SCHIFRIN: Thanks, Gwen.

43:38.115 --> 43:45.490 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: From the very
opening of the
telecast last night, much of the
focus during

43:45.523 --> 43:50.061 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Academy Awards was on
Hollywood's problems
with diversity.

43:50.094 --> 43:55.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But near the end, a notable
upset also garnered
some attention. The movie
"Spotlight" won

43:55.700 --> 44:01.639 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for best picture. In part, it is
a reminder
about the state of investigative
journalism,

44:01.672 --> 44:06.844 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
