work to do.

46:31.155 --> 46:35.993 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And yet we have to commit
ourselves to doing
it. Somebody needs to hold
powerful institutions

46:36.027 --> 46:41.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and individuals accountable, and
we're the
ones who have that particular
role in our

46:41.999 --> 46:43.868 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
society.

46:43.901 --> 46:48.305 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: The Boston
Globe's "Spotlight"
unit won a Pulitzer Prize for
its coverage.

46:48.339 --> 46:53.878 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To add to Martin Baron's point
about economic
pressures, since 2003, newspaper
staffs have

46:53.911 --> 46:59.250 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
